frameDefinitions: An Agent or a Cause mentally or physically expends energy rendering an Input, whether implicit or explicit, into a Output.
A Material is used to make a Product.
An Owner has (or lacks) a Possession. '' 'The river's part of my  manor, but of course it also belongs to the River Police.'
A Process stops at a certain Time and Place.
A Text is an entity that contains linguistic, symbolic information on a Topic, created by an Author at the Time_of_creation.
A physical object, the Artifact, is produced by a Creator to stimulate the perceptions, emotions, or cognition of an audience.
frameExamples: Erosion is the <t>work</t> of wind and water on rock.
These cooking <t><fex name='mat'>ingredients</fex></t> are readily available.
The river's part of my  manor, but of course it also <t>belongs</t> to the River Police.
Sir Denis Mahon is the owner of the most important private collection of Italian Baroque <t><fex name='Artifact'>paintings</fex></t>.
listRoleDefinitions: A sentient entity whose physical and mental faculties are directly expended on the <fen>Input</fen> to create the <fen>Output</fen>.
A non-sentient entity whose physical faculties are directly expended on the <fen>Input</fen> to create the <fen>Output</fen>.
The mental or physical faculties onto which the <fen>Agent</fen> or <fen>Cause</fen> expends energy.
The end product, either a concept or physical object onto which the <fen>Agent</fen> or <fen>Cause</fen> has exerted its mental or physical faculties from the rudimentary state of <fen>Input</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Output</fen> was committed into reality.
The place where the <fen>Output</fen> was birthed.
The entity which is used to make a <fen>Product</fen>.
The purpose for which the <fen>Material</fen> is intended.
The entity or substance that is created out of the <fen>Material</fen>.
The entity that owns a posession.

The thing which is owned by the Owner.
Ex.:  I <t>have</t> <fex name='Possession'>twenty bucks</fex>.
(This does not include bodyparts or medical conditions, but does include intellectual property, etc.)
This role indicates the <fen>Time</fen> interval during which the <fen>Owner</fen> has a possession.
The <fen>Text</fen> is the entity that contains linguistic information. This an incorporated role for each LU in this frame.
The region where the <fen>Text</fen> is sold, circulated, or otherwise popular.
This role identifies the entity or substance that is designed to have a particular <fen>Use</fen>.
The location where the <fen>Artifact</fen> is presently located.
listRoleExamples: Add all the <fex>ingredients</fex>, toss and chill.
Supply and placing of <fex>building</fex> materials shall be incidental to installation of the paving stones.
The first of the two <fex>drawings</fex> by Parmigianino recently acquired for the National Gallery is a study for the Madonna dal collo lungo.
